@NODE Function
@PREV Install
@NEXT License
@TOC MAIN

            @{B} CONTROL VINFO @{UB}
 In the top of the screen there is a menustrip with simple functions.
 Vinfo is simply using the mouse and the keyboard , you click at the
 desired function with the mouse and voila ! 

 You use the mouse in the following way.

       * Left mouse button to choose a function.
       * Right mouse button to choose a menustrip.
    
            @{B} EDIT TEXT @{UB}
 Vinfo has very primitive text edit function, you simply edit a line and
 then select the colour and text font, and that's it !, You can't do 
 any fancy text editing, but there is no need for that !

            @{B} INVOKE PICTURES @{UB}
 You can choose if you want a TEXT page or PICTURE page, in a future version
 they can be mixed, so pictures can be used as backgrounds.

            @{B} VINFO INFO @{UB}
       * PAL/NTSC System using locale Language.
       * 30 pages with indivudually set delay between 10 or 120 sec.
       * 5 different fonts ,about 20 pixels max height.
       * 16 rows of text. 7 Text colours , including one "flash" colour.
       * Picture resolution is about 320x256 , in 128 colours.
       * Backgound Logo 320x256 in 64 colours.
       * Text can be saved on hardisk/disk etc, in case of crash :-(

            @{B} EXIT VINFO @{UB}
 Uuups, forgot about that, eh when in "show" mode, press escape key !!
