@NODE Advanced
@PREV License
@NEXT Future
@TOC MAIN


 @{B} How to set up a system for a customer @{UB}

 Vinfo works on any A1200 or better. It was developed on a Amiga4000/040.
 It is very easy to set up a customer system, it is enough with a A1200
 with one diskdrive , this gives a very low price for the hardware !
 You could create a disk with Vinfo and some gfx , setup the startup
 so it copies all gfx to ram: then run Vinfo ,Voila !

 Remember to make to it easy for the customer, so you don't need to spend
 any extra time reinstalling software etc. You should create a disk that
 autoboots and loads everything , so that in case of a crash the result
 is only a minor delay of time. The best thing is when everything else
 is closed down, like wb screen and such things. And use the RAM: so
 (In case of no hardisk!) , loading time is kept at minimum.
 
 Vinfo is not using anything else than the Amiga OS , for a list you can
 take a look at @{" System resources used " link System}
 
@{B} Vinfo looks for a file Vinfo.Logo @{UB}
 If there is a picture file 320x256 ,64 colours with the name Vinfo.Logo
 then this is used as a constant background. If this file is not present
 then this screen is not setup, thus saving some bus cycles , this does
 possible speed up the operation of the screen swapping a bit.

@{B} Vinfo looks for your .GFX files @{UB}
 When Vinfo starts , either from CLI or WB , it scans the current
 directory and the ram: for all files ending with .GFX , thus you can 
 place all your gfx files there and name them .GFX , since Vinfo is using
 datatypes it can handle a lot of different formats, but remember that the 
 resolution and the amount of colours are limited to 320x256 in 128 colours.
 NOTE !! , the first 8 colours are used by the system , therefore you can
 not use them, since I don't do any palette remapping!

@{B} Vinfo can be made "Solo system"  @{UB}

 If you start Vinfo with a parameter SOLO,then Vinfo tries to take over the
 machine. This is a very useful for a end customer system. The following
 is happens when this parameter is set. 

 1. Escape key disabled, so no escape is possible
 2. Vinfo tries to be the constant foremost screen.
 3. Vinfo tries to be the constant owner of the user.
 4. Vinfo tries to close the WB screen.

 At startup Vinfo tries to close the WB , but it can only do that if
 there is no CLI window open, so you should close the CLI directly after
 that you have started VINFO,  NOTE !! , A small delay (About 5 sec) at
 startup , so you can close the shell that started Vinfo, so Vinfo can
 close WB screen !!.



